# Paste the Blotato API key EXACTLY as shown in the Blotato dashboard.
# Do NOT add or remove any characters (including any trailing "="). The client trims
# only surrounding whitespace/newlines. A wrong-length key returns 401.
BLOTATO_API_KEY=
# Backend: dryrun | rest | mcp (Blotato) | postiz (free, self-hosted)  (defaults to dryrun)
FANOPS_POSTER=dryrun
# FREE publishing via a self-hosted Postiz instance (github.com/gitroomhq/postiz-app) — set
# FANOPS_POSTER=postiz and fill both. POSTIZ_URL = your instance base (e.g. https://api.postiz.com);
# POSTIZ_API_KEY from Postiz Settings > Developers > Public API. Connect each fan account inside
# Postiz, and put its INTEGRATION id into accounts.json `account_id`. No Blotato account/key needed.
# POSTIZ_URL=
# POSTIZ_API_KEY=
# Agent-gate responder: manual | llm  (manual = a human/cron writes response files)
FANOPS_RESPONDER=manual
# NOT required. The autonomous responder (FANOPS_RESPONDER=llm) shells plain `claude -p` (NOT
# `--bare`), so it uses your EXISTING Claude subscription / `claude login` session — no API key.
# Run `claude login` once on the host; cron inherits it. (With FANOPS_RESPONDER=llm, `fanops
# advance`/`run` HARD-FAIL (exit 2) only if `claude` is NOT on PATH — see RUNTIME.md.) You may set
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY for a 3P/Bedrock setup if you prefer, but it is not needed for the subscription.
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# Optional: artist DISPLAY NAME used as the YouTube title fallback (default "Moh Flow").
# Set this when running FanOps for a different artist. Distinct from the @mohflow caption mention.
# FANOPS_ARTIST_NAME=Moh Flow

# Zernio TikTok upload cap (MB). Files over this are auto-shrunk before publish; DEFAULT 4.
# FANOPS_ZERNIO_MAX_UPLOAD_MB=4
